🔥 INCIDENT 12: Disk Full → Application Crash
🔹 Incident Summary

Application suddenly stopped working.

Users getting:

500 Internal Server Error

or

Application unavailable

Server is UP.

SSH works.

Application is DOWN.

🧠 What Actually Happened (Simple Story)

Application continuously writes:

Logs
Temp files
Cache files

Disk reached:

100% Used

Now application cannot write new data.

Application crashes.

🔄 Real Workflow
Users → Application
              ↓
          Write Logs
              ↓
         Disk 100% Full
              ↓
       Application Crash
🧪 Step-by-Step Troubleshooting
1️⃣ Login Server
ssh ec2-user@server-ip
2️⃣ Check Disk Usage
df -h

Example:

/dev/xvda1  20G  20G  0G  100%

Problem found.

3️⃣ Find Large Directories
du -sh /*

or

du -sh /var/*
4️⃣ Find Large Files
find / -type f -size +500M
5️⃣ Check Logs
cd /var/log
du -sh *

Often:

app.log = 15GB
🔍 ROOT CAUSE

Most common:

Log rotation missing
Huge application logs
Backup files accumulating
Temp files not cleaned
✅ QUICK FIX

Delete old logs:

rm -f app.log.old

or

truncate -s 0 app.log

Restart application:

systemctl restart myapp
🛡️ PERMANENT FIX

Install logrotate:

yum install logrotate -y

Configure:

/etc/logrotate.d/myapp

Increase EBS volume if needed.

🎯 Interview Answer

"When application crashes unexpectedly, I first check disk utilization using df -h. If the filesystem is full, I identify large files using du and find commands. After clearing space and restarting the application, I implement log rotation and monitoring to prevent recurrence."

